The paper deals with codes and their properties, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC) sub-categories. The use of group rings suggests a connection to algebraic structures, which is relevant to the group theory (cs.GT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper establishes the structures of reversible and complementary dual checkable codes, which may be of interest to researchers in the cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category.
